commentPreTextItems.html: Match State: Match start scheduled for 10.45am local time (9.45am GMT)
Good Morning, its the NatWest Series last league match today with West Indies and New Zealand at The Main Oval, Hampshire Rose Bowl, Southampton
Today match has turned into a mini-final, and a chance for both teams to win an important psychological victory before the Lord's final on Saturday
Both the teams will look to go to the final on a winning note
There is overnight rain in Southampton, which means that although the ground is well covered, it is going to take a considerable time to make it fit for play
There will be an inspection at 11:30 local time (10:30 GMT)
Match State: Delay - inspection at 11:30 local time (10:30 GMT)
Match State: Delay - Rain
Latest update: 12.30 pm (local time) 11:30 gmt inspection was cancelled
all the covers are now on and it is raining
Update: 02:00 local time (13:00 GMT) - Its now stopped raining
Match State: Delay - Damp Conditions
the rain has stopped, but the heavy covers remain
Some of the covers have been taken off, and the groundstaff are using various pieces of equipment to try and dry out the outfield
Latest update: Inspection at 3:00pm local time (2:00pm gmt)
Welcome back
Umpire Harper says if there is no further rain, play can start at 1630 BST (1530 GMT).
That will give us a 20-over a side match
With the rain still coming down the umpires have decided to an end to the days play
Please join us for the final on July 10 at 09:45GMT from Lord's between New Zealand and West Indies

notes: West Indies won the toss and elected to field

Under a decision made by the ICC Chief Executives' Committee on June 30th 2004, "all future Test and ODI matches that are abandoned without a ball being bowled shall be included in the records provided the toss has taken place."
